      <title>Letter, Rev. J.R. Bain in Gallatin, Tenn., to J.G.M. Ramsey in Knoxville, Tenn. 1823 June 20</title>
   </titleInfo>
   <abstract>1823 June 20 Rev. J.R. Bain, Gallatin, Tenn., to Dr. J.G.M. Ramsey, Knoxville, Tenn. In reply to Dr. Ramsey&apos;s letter of May 29, 1823, relays information concerning Mecklenburg Convention gathered from Zacheras Wilson. Urges Dr. Ramsey not to be discouraged by unchristian behavior in others but to set a Christian example himself. Refers to the 1824 presidential election.</abstract>
